flowchart TD
%% Mikado graph for stateful process contracts (GitHub #34) — `Bond.Server`.
%%
%% A GenServer module does `use GenServer` + `use Bond.Server` and declares
%% module-wide, state-centric contracts that Bond checks around the server's
%% state-transition callbacks:
%%   @state_invariant      <label>: <expr over `state`>
%%       — checked after every transition callback returns (and after init/1
%%         and code_change/3 establish a new state).
%%   @transition_invariant <label>: <expr over `old_state` and `new_state`>
%%       — checked across every transition that has a comparable prior state
%%         (every callback EXCEPT init/1 and code_change/3).
%%
%% Mechanism reuses Bond wholesale: the @on_definition compiler hook records the
%% user's callbacks (NOT def-shadowing; and overridable? must NOT gate capture —
%% a user's handle_call fires overridable?=true because it overrides GenServer's
%% default), @before_compile emits a defoverridable + wrapper-def + super around
%% each, the wrapper pulls the new state out of the return tuple via
%% Bond.Server.Runtime.extract_state/2, and the existing check_assertion / Eval
%% gate / failure-raise machinery does the rest. Gated under the :invariants kind
%% (zero new Bond.Config surface). Spike: spikes/server_defoverridable/ (GO).
%%
%% Shipped as TWO minors: Slice 1 = @state_invariant (safety net, quiet release);
%% Slice 2 = @transition_invariant (marquee, forum-announced). Each numbered node
%% is a commit-sized step; arrows point from a goal to its prerequisites; leaves
%% (green) are safe to start. Depth-first: pick a leaf, finish it, commit, repeat.
%% Every commit compiles and the suite stays green.

    G(["**Goal**<br/>Stateful process contracts (#34)"])

    %% ---- Slice 1: @state_invariant (first minor) ----
    GS1(["**Slice 1**<br/>@state_invariant on every transition callback"])
    G --> GS1

    GS1 --> S7[S7. Docs: concurrency-guide rewrite + public-api StateInvariantError + getting-started + CHANGELOG]
    S7 --> S6[S6. Tests: inline-mutation catch, init/code_change creation-check, all callbacks, :invariants gating, use-order]
    S6 --> S5[S5. before_compile: defoverridable + wrapper-def + super per user callback, extract_state, run state-invariant, gate :invariants]
    S5 --> S4[S4. Bond.Server.Runtime.extract_state/2 — per-callback return-shape matcher]
    S5 --> S3[S3. Lifted __bond_state_invariants__/1 defp reusing check_assertion, kind :state_invariant]
    S5 --> SE[SE. Bond.StateInvariantError struct + eval @assertion_errors entry]
    S3 --> S2[S2. Capture @state_invariant AST via @-override clause + __bond_state_invariants__ reflection]
    S2 --> S1[S1. Bond.Server skeleton: @on_definition + @before_compile, record user callbacks, __bond_server_callbacks__ reflection]
    S4 --> M
    S1 --> M[M. Mikado graph]
    SE --> M

    %% ---- Slice 2: @transition_invariant (second minor, marquee) ----
    GS2(["**Slice 2**<br/>@transition_invariant across every transition"])
    G --> GS2

    GS2 --> H5[H5. Docs: temporal-constraints section + public-api TransitionInvariantError + CHANGELOG + forum announcement]
    H5 --> H4[H4. Tests: monotonic catch on inline cast, init/code_change skip, old vs new threading]
    H4 --> H3[H3. Wrap: bind old=incoming state, call __bond_transition_invariants__ old,new; init/code_change omit]
    H3 --> H2[H2. Lifted __bond_transition_invariants__/2 defp, old_state/new_state bindings]
    H2 --> H1[H1. Capture @transition_invariant AST via @-override clause + reflection fn]
    H3 --> HE[HE. Bond.TransitionInvariantError struct + eval @assertion_errors entry]
    H1 --> S2
    H3 --> S5

    %% ---- v2 / stretch ----
    GV(["**v2 / stretch**"])
    G --> GV
    GV --> V1[V1. Bond.PropertyTest server sequence runner — start server, drive calls/casts, wrapped callbacks are the oracle]
    V1 --> GS2

    classDef leaf fill:#e7f5e7,stroke:#2e7d32,stroke-width:2px;
    class M,SE,S1,S4 leaf;

    style G fill:#90EE90
    style GS1 fill:#cfe8cf
    style GS2 fill:#cfe8cf
    style GV fill:#cfe8cf
    style M fill:#90EE90
    style SE fill:#90EE90
    style S1 fill:#90EE90
    style S4 fill:#90EE90
